TUX_SWIMS README:

_______________________TUX SWIMS_______________________
"TUX_SWIMS" is a little 2D-game about TUX (who swims from Antarctic to Africa) and see a lot of things from the big "Software-World". 

_______________________HOW TO RUN_______________________
"TUX_SWIMS" comes with no application to install and it can not run by it self.
You need "Python3", "IDLE 3" and "Pygame" to run and edit "TUX_SWIMS".
Install "Python3", "IDLE 3" and "Pygame" with:
|apt-get install python3|
|apt-get install python-pygame|
|apt-get install IDLE3|
|apt-get update|


_______________________SOFTWARE & HARDWARE_______________________
HARDWARE:
You need a "normal" PC-Setup, a Monitor with min 1920px × 1080px,
a CPU comparable to an Intel Core i3 and 4GiB RAM.

The developer used:
8 GiB RAM
Intel Core i5-3570 CPU (4 × 3.40GHz) 
Nvidia GeForce GTX 760 GPU

SOFTWARE:
You need a GNU/Linux Desktop-OS comparable to Debian with a GUI (Gnome, KDE, LXDE, Unity, Xfce...) that is able to run Python 3 and IDLE 3.

The developer used:
Debian GNU/Linux 8 (jessie) 64-Bit with Gnome 3

